external_knowledge:
- "Stars in the game" refers to players;
- "Outshone their peers" means scoring more points than the average points scored by all players;
- "Stellar performance" refers to the number of points scored.

- "Average points per game" refers to the total points scored divided by the number of games played;
- "Position on the court" refers to the roles such as Point Guard (PG), Shooting Guard (SG), Small Forward (SF), Power Forward (PF), and Center (C);
- "Reigns supreme in scoring" means the position with the highest average points.

- 'Rankings within the position' refers to the player's standing compared to others in the same position based on points, rebounds, and assists;
- 'Average statistics for their position' are the mean values of points, rebounds, and assists for all players in the same position;
- 'Detailed statistics' include points, rebounds, assists, steals, blocks, turnovers, field goal percentage, three-point percentage, and free throw percentage.

- "standout players" refers to players who are ranked first in at least one of the following categories: average points, wins, or games played;
- "average points" is the mean number of points scored by a player in a season;
- "wins" are the number of games won by a player in a season;
- "games played" is the total number of games a player has participated in during a season.

sql:
SELECT player_id, games_played, points
FROM players_statistics
WHERE points > 20;

SELECT points
FROM statistics
ORDER BY points DESC;

